00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:17,240
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

270
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:20,360
I’ll have three pork skewers
and one packet of sticky rice.

271
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:21,320
Sure.

272
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:23,040
(Pork skewers)

273
00:14:23,040 --> 00:14:24,640
Popular shops are like this.

274
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:25,520
Thank you.

275
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:29,640
Oh, Aunt Noy, it’s you.

276
00:14:29,880 --> 00:14:33,000
I’ll have four pork skewers
and one packet of sticky rice.

277
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:35,640
- Sure.
- And Aunt Noy wants...

278
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:38,320
- I’ll take five.
- Five pork skewers, please.

279
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:40,360
- Sure.
- So it’s a total of two orders.

280
00:14:40,440 --> 00:14:42,300
One order is four pork skewers
and one packet of sticky rice.

281
00:14:42,300 --> 00:14:43,760
And the other is five pork skewers.

282
00:14:47,040 --> 00:14:48,200
- Here.
- Thank you.

283
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:48,960
It’s alright.

284
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,520
Here’s yours, auntie.

285
00:15:09,680 --> 00:15:12,120
Oh, you’re back?

286
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:20,360
You don’t want me to come back?
Alright, I’ll go.

287
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:21,600
Wait, hold on.

288
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:25,680
I didn’t mean that.

289
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:29,640
I bought you some pork skewers.

290
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:32,720
Hey, pork skewers.

291
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:34,480
How did you get it?

292
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:36,800
This shop always has a long queue.

293
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:46,000
Do you buy this for
every experimental partner of yours?

294
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:50,040
It’s your favorite.
I bought it only for you.

295
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:54,920
How about Meena?

296
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,520
Meena is just helping me
with my research.

297
00:15:58,640 --> 00:15:59,840
That’s all.

298
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:01,160
And this mark here,

299
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:03,400
Meena accidentally crashed into me.

300
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:08,360
I didn’t ask you.

301
00:16:08,880 --> 00:16:10,880
Why do you have to explain it to me?

302
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:16,600
So you’re not mad at me anymore?

303
00:16:17,040 --> 00:16:18,040
No.

304
00:16:21,280 --> 00:16:23,400
(Rules of living together)

305
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:30,320
But if you don’t want me to be mad,
it’s not that difficult.

306
00:16:32,360 --> 00:16:33,360
How so?

307
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:35,240
You will have to cancel all the rules.

308
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:38,720
And let me put some of my stuff

309
00:16:38,720 --> 00:16:39,920
in this living room too.

310
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:49,360
Um.

311
00:16:50,640 --> 00:16:51,720
Alright.

312
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:52,480
Yay.

313
00:17:09,120 --> 00:17:12,360
Why am I happy seeing it today?

314
00:17:13,360 --> 00:17:15,400
I’m taking over this room.

315
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:16,480
I’m telling you,

316
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:19,400
everything in this room is mine.

317
00:17:25,960 --> 00:17:27,400
I’m

318
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:30,400
in this room too.

319
00:17:58,520 --> 00:18:01,000
Why are you up so early?

320
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:06,280
What’s going on?

321
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:10,320
(Mom)

322
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:15,760
Hello, mom.

323
00:18:15,760 --> 00:18:17,920
Prapai, what is going on?

324
00:18:17,920 --> 00:18:21,280
How have you been? I’m very shocked.

325
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:26,160
I told you Bangkok is very dangerous.

326
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:27,720
Come back home, dear.

327
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:30,560
Hold on, calm down first.

328
00:18:30,840 --> 00:18:32,160
What’s going on?

329
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:36,160
Isn’t the girl in the news, you?

330
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:39,320
Peng showed me the photos.

331
00:18:39,320 --> 00:18:41,040
It looks just like you.

332
00:18:41,360 --> 00:18:42,560
What news?

333
00:18:43,520 --> 00:18:45,160
(Male celebrity named T.)

334
00:18:45,160 --> 00:18:47,160
(Drugged a mysterious girl
to take her back to his place)

335
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:49,840
What? Why is the news like this?

336
00:18:50,400 --> 00:18:52,440
And so is it really you?

337
00:18:52,480 --> 00:18:53,680
I know it’s you

338
00:18:53,680 --> 00:18:55,200
just seeing you from behind.

339
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:58,360
Calm down first, mom.

340
00:18:58,360 --> 00:19:00,600
It’s not like what the news reported.

341
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:03,640
Time is a celebrity
that I am taking care of.

342
00:19:03,640 --> 00:19:05,920
And there was a celebration after work.

343
00:19:05,960 --> 00:19:07,960
And I was drunk.

344
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:10,640
No, I was just a bit tipsy.

345
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:14,600
Time just wanted to drop me off
at the condominium.

346
00:19:15,080 --> 00:19:17,400
But he didn’t drop me off, mom.

347
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:19,440
No one drugged anyone.

348
00:19:19,440 --> 00:19:21,880
And no one carried anyone
back to their places.

349
00:19:22,240 --> 00:19:23,960
How can the reporters do that?

350
00:19:24,280 --> 00:19:28,000
Wait, hold on.
And is Time hitting on you?

351
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:34,600
Mom, it’s getting ridiculous.

352
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:37,760
We’re just working together.

353
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:39,040
He’s not hitting on you,

354
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:41,680
but why does he have to drop you off?

355
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:44,760
I can tell if a guy is tricking you.

356
00:19:45,440 --> 00:19:46,280
But

357
00:19:47,240 --> 00:19:50,480
Pai, this guy though,

358
00:19:50,520 --> 00:19:52,080
he’s quite popular.

359
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:55,880
You can actually talk with him.
I don’t see any problem with it.

360
00:19:58,080 --> 00:20:00,760
Are you with a guy?
Who’s voice was that?

361
00:20:00,760 --> 00:20:02,520
It’s...

362
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:04,440
It’s the television, mom.

363
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:07,040
You don’t have to worry about the news.

364
00:20:07,040 --> 00:20:10,400
I’m all good. I’m safe.

365
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:13,760
I have to go now. Bye.

366
00:20:13,760 --> 00:20:15,800
Hey, hey. Pai. Pai.

367
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:34,560
Hello.

368
00:20:34,560 --> 00:20:35,760
Hey, hey.

369
00:20:35,760 --> 00:20:37,600
You’re not living with a guy, right?

370
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:39,080
Yes, I’m sure.

371
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:41,920
Then turn on FaceTime.

372
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:43,280
Right now?

373
00:20:43,280 --> 00:20:46,720
Yes, right now.
Or are you hiding something?

374
00:20:47,320 --> 00:20:48,520
No, I’m not.

375
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,320
I’ll turn on the camera.

376
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:55,520
See, mom? I’m alone.

377
00:20:56,480 --> 00:20:57,840
I’m not hiding anything.

378
00:20:59,080 --> 00:21:00,660
Your room is very clean.

379
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:02,760
Unlike when you’re at home.

380
00:21:03,280 --> 00:21:05,680
But look at that.

381
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:07,800
There’re still things everywhere.

382
00:21:07,840 --> 00:21:08,860
You’re exactly the same.

383
00:21:08,860 --> 00:21:10,240
Just like you used to be.

384
00:21:10,760 --> 00:21:14,240
So if you don’t have anything else,
I have to go now.

385
00:21:14,880 --> 00:21:15,920
Bye, mom.

386
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:17,000
Hey.

387
00:21:23,680 --> 00:21:26,520
Hello, mom,
I told you no one drugged me.

388
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:28,620
I want to hear an explanation
about this as well.

389
00:21:28,780 --> 00:21:30,160
Come to the office right now.

390
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:39,560
I don’t know what the real story is.

391
00:21:39,560 --> 00:21:42,480
And I don’t want to know
what’s going on between you two.

392
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:45,360
But this will have negative effects
for sure.

393
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:48,720
Our client is quite upset about it.

394
00:21:48,920 --> 00:21:49,500
That their presenter

395
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:51,200
is having a bad reputation
because of our staff.

396
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:55,840
Alright. So during this time,
you can go do other jobs first.

397
00:21:56,320 --> 00:21:58,120
- But it’s really...
- And if there’s nothing necessary,

398
00:21:58,760 --> 00:22:00,560
don’t be in contact with Time anymore.

399
00:22:02,320 --> 00:22:03,240
Yes.

400
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:07,140
I didn’t want to do this.

401
00:22:07,540 --> 00:22:08,560
You understand me, right?

402
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:11,240
I understand.

403
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:14,120
Alright. Then that’s it.

404
00:22:15,160 --> 00:22:17,320
Thank you. Thank you.

405
00:22:32,480 --> 00:22:33,700
(I’m sorry I got you in trouble.)

406
00:22:33,700 --> 00:22:34,760
(I really am.)

407
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:36,440
(If it weren’t for me,
this wouldn’t have happened.)

408
00:22:41,320 --> 00:22:42,680
(Man Manager)

409
00:22:46,720 --> 00:22:47,880
Hello, Man.

410
00:22:47,880 --> 00:22:48,640
Time.

411
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:50,640
Why weren’t you careful?

412
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:52,520
Oh boy.

413
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:55,760
Why do you complain so much?

414
00:22:56,360 --> 00:22:59,000
I’m in the spotlight.
It’s not weird to be having rumors.

415
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:00,600
You’re still joking around?

416
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:02,880
Never mind about it.

417
00:23:04,120 --> 00:23:05,360
Oh, Man.

418
00:23:05,720 --> 00:23:07,440
I want you to help me with something.

419
00:23:07,440 --> 00:23:08,720
What else do you what?

420
00:23:09,480 --> 00:23:11,600
It’s about the person from the rumor.

421
00:23:16,520 --> 00:23:17,680
I thought she was decent.

422
00:23:17,680 --> 00:23:18,760
You don’t say that.

423
00:23:24,440 --> 00:23:25,320
Look at her.

424
00:23:26,480 --> 00:23:27,720
Acting to be innocent in front of men.

425
00:23:29,720 --> 00:23:31,880
What’s wrong? Look at what she did.

426
00:23:31,880 --> 00:23:33,640
- Unbelievable.
- I know, right?

427
00:23:33,880 --> 00:23:36,600
Some people are so shameful.

428
00:23:36,840 --> 00:23:38,760
Never stop talking and gossiping.

429
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:40,320
Keep on talking behind people’s back.

430
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:46,360
All the annoying people are gone.

431
00:23:46,360 --> 00:23:47,840
It’s only me.

432
00:23:48,020 --> 00:23:49,840
Tell me what happened.

433
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:53,520
What can it be? It’s a misunderstanding.

434
00:23:54,160 --> 00:23:55,800
No one drugged me.

435
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:58,120
I’m just not good with alcohol.

436
00:23:59,680 --> 00:24:03,120
Time just wanted to drop me off.
But now he has to face all this.

437
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:05,440
Keep it down.

438
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:07,920
There’re people envying you
from everywhere.

439
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:10,520
Anyone would want a moment like this.

440
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:13,080
Going viral with a celebrity.

441
00:24:13,840 --> 00:24:17,320
Just like being the main character
in a Chinese series.

442
00:24:18,680 --> 00:24:21,240
Hold on. If you don’t feel anything.

443
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:24,160
That means you already have
someone you like.

444
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:32,520
(Pupaa)

445
00:24:35,240 --> 00:24:36,280
Hello, Pupaa.

446
00:24:37,120 --> 00:24:38,440
I’m in front of your office.

447
00:24:38,640 --> 00:24:39,920
I brought you some brownies.

448
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:40,840
Come get it.

449
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:44,000
Sure, wait a moment.

450
00:24:45,280 --> 00:24:46,120
I’ll be back.

451
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:58,360
Hey.

452
00:24:58,560 --> 00:24:59,360
Here you go.

453
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,680
Thank you.

454
00:25:01,920 --> 00:25:02,840
Look.

455
00:25:02,840 --> 00:25:03,800
Look at that.

456
00:25:03,800 --> 00:25:05,840
Went viral with a celebrity
in the morning,

457
00:25:05,840 --> 00:25:07,800
now a good looking guy
is bringing her snacks in the afternoon.

458
00:25:07,840 --> 00:25:09,080
She looks so innocent.

459
00:25:09,080 --> 00:25:11,520
- Who would’ve known she’s such a bitch.
- You’re so right.

460
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:29,480
Prapai.

461
00:25:30,760 --> 00:25:31,880
Take this too.

462
00:25:32,560 --> 00:25:34,000
So you can’t hear others.

463
00:25:46,040 --> 00:25:47,440
What should I do?

464
00:25:47,440 --> 00:25:50,920
It’s like I’m falling for him
more and more every day.

465
00:26:00,680 --> 00:26:03,960
(Time)

466
00:26:12,880 --> 00:26:13,800
Hello.

467
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:15,720
Why aren’t you at the set today?

468
00:26:16,640 --> 00:26:18,760
It’s such a viral.

469
00:26:18,760 --> 00:26:20,960
Who would let me be near you?

470
00:26:21,120 --> 00:26:22,480
Oh wow.

471
00:26:22,840 --> 00:26:24,640
Are we forced to be separate?

472
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:28,680
It’s a huge problem
and you’re still joking about it?

473
00:26:28,880 --> 00:26:31,320
Okay. I’ll stop.

474
00:26:31,480 --> 00:26:33,040
I’m going to be serious now.

475
00:26:33,680 --> 00:26:36,440
So after this incident,
you plan on hiding away from me, right?

476
00:26:36,880 --> 00:26:38,560
No, I’m not.

477
00:26:38,560 --> 00:26:40,080
Don’t give me an excuse.

478
00:26:40,760 --> 00:26:43,880
You texted me only once
and you disappeared.

479
00:26:44,240 --> 00:26:45,720
If I didn’t call,

480
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:47,040
you wouldn’t have said anything, right?

481
00:26:48,800 --> 00:26:50,920
I guess you’re just apologizing
for the sake of it.

482
00:26:51,520 --> 00:26:53,240
It’s not like that.

483
00:26:53,440 --> 00:26:54,320
Pon won’t let me...

484
00:26:54,320 --> 00:26:55,880
Otherwise,

485
00:26:55,880 --> 00:26:57,120
come meet me.

486
00:26:58,160 --> 00:27:01,000
How can I go? The news is still viral.

487
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:03,640
If I go and the reporters see me,

488
00:27:03,640 --> 00:27:06,440
it’ll be a bigger problem,
and I’ll be in bigger trouble.

489
00:27:06,440 --> 00:27:09,120
- And you’ll be having worse rumors.
- Blah, blah, blah.

490
00:27:09,120 --> 00:27:11,960
You keep complaining like my manager.

491
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:14,880
We can meet in a place
where nobody’s around.

492
00:27:15,840 --> 00:27:17,280
Is that possible?

493
00:27:17,840 --> 00:27:20,040
Wherever you go, people always notice.

494
00:27:21,320 --> 00:27:22,360
There sure is.

495
00:27:22,840 --> 00:27:24,160
You’ll know when you get here.

496
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:30,200
What is wrong with him?

497
00:27:31,760 --> 00:27:33,320
So stubborn.

498
00:27:38,140 --> 00:27:41,260
(STORYBOARD)

499
00:27:58,800 --> 00:28:00,640
Are your legs too short?
That’s why you’re here late.

500
00:28:01,840 --> 00:28:03,440
Stop talking.

501
00:28:16,360 --> 00:28:19,040
There’s no one around here
to gossip about us, just like you said.

502
00:28:20,720 --> 00:28:22,800
I like to come here during my free time.

503
00:28:23,760 --> 00:28:25,000
I can’t believe

504
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:27,560
that a celebrity like you
has this kind of moment.

505
00:28:30,520 --> 00:28:31,840
I’ve got many more.

506
00:28:32,960 --> 00:28:34,480
Do you want to know me more?

507
00:28:35,760 --> 00:28:36,800
Hey.

508
00:28:37,320 --> 00:28:37,840
Don’t do this.

509
00:28:37,840 --> 00:28:40,240
There’ll be more rumors going around.

510
00:28:40,360 --> 00:28:43,760
I will affect your future. Be careful.

511
00:28:56,840 --> 00:28:57,840
I’m sorry.

512
00:29:00,040 --> 00:29:01,720
What’s with you today?

513
00:29:01,960 --> 00:29:03,720
Why are you apologizing to me?

514
00:29:05,800 --> 00:29:08,160
Sorry for getting you in trouble.

515
00:29:08,400 --> 00:29:10,480
I’m not in that much trouble.

516
00:29:10,640 --> 00:29:12,440
You’re the one in trouble.

517
00:29:16,920 --> 00:29:18,160
I’m a celebrity.

518
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:20,040
I’m used to this.

519
00:29:21,400 --> 00:29:22,140
But you.

520
00:29:22,380 --> 00:29:24,400
I guess people have been
gossiping about you a lot.

521
00:29:26,520 --> 00:29:28,920
No one’s numb with things like this.

522
00:29:31,800 --> 00:29:33,840
But those words and accusations

523
00:29:33,840 --> 00:29:36,320
don’t even consider any reasonings.

524
00:29:36,320 --> 00:29:38,640
Even if it’s someone crazy like you.

525
00:29:38,640 --> 00:29:40,560
But you’ve got feelings.

526
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:43,120
Having to hear it so often,

527
00:29:43,120 --> 00:29:45,560
I’m sure it hurts.

528
00:29:48,920 --> 00:29:51,440
Back in the days, I never understood

529
00:29:51,440 --> 00:29:53,600
how these comments and rumors

530
00:29:53,600 --> 00:29:55,840
can hurt our feelings.

531
00:29:56,560 --> 00:29:58,200
But now...

532
00:30:03,520 --> 00:30:05,400
Being you isn’t so easy I guess.

533
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:29,000
I don’t care little issues like this.

534
00:30:34,160 --> 00:30:35,360
But I have one way

535
00:30:35,360 --> 00:30:37,080
that can help you feel better.

536
00:30:40,800 --> 00:30:41,680
What is it?

537
00:30:48,520 --> 00:30:50,680
How can you trust those rumors?

538
00:30:50,680 --> 00:30:52,600
It’s not even true.

539
00:30:52,840 --> 00:30:56,120
